    "instructions": "Combine vinegar, water, sugar, salt, and vegetable broth in a pot and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes. For Thermomix, cook for 6 minutes. Afterward, add the remaining ingredients and mix with a hand blender for 5-8 seconds. For Thermomix, mix for 10 seconds on speed 5. Pour the dressing into bottles and store in the refrigerator once cooled. The vinegar preserves the dressing, making it last long. This dressing is great for all leafy salads or raw vegetables.",
